                  <additions><list><item xml:id="e1">20th-c  notes: F. 132,Daggāzmāc Wasan Saggad (baptismal name Walda Gabre'ēl) owned the ms before Ato Gabra Giyorgis gave it to Makāna Śellāsē of Addis Ababa; f 214b, donation dated to 1900 EC (1907/8 A.D.); Wasan Saggad son of Sawāragā and Daggāzmāc Wadāgo.</item></list></additions>
               </physDesc>
               <history>
                  <provenance>Note of ownership by ወልደ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ወሰን፡ ሰገድ፡ and his father ቴዎድሮስ, fol. 1v; 20th century note states that this manuscript was owned by ደጃዝማች፡ ወሰን፡ ሰገድ, whose baptismal name was ወልደ ገብርኤል and is the son of ሰዋረጋ daughter of Emperor Menilek II and his father was ደጃዝማች፡ ወዳጆ son of ራስ፡ ጎበና, and this manuscript was given to Makāna Śellāsē church of Addis Ababa by አቶ፡ ገብረ፡ ጊዮርጊስ in 1900 EC, fol. 132v and 214v; Seals of ደጃዝማች፡ ወሰን፡ ሰገድ, ገብረ፡ ጊዮርጊስ, and Holy Trinity Cathedral throughout</provenance>
               </history>
