               <msPart xml:id="p1">
                  <msIdentifier>
                     <collection>Addis Ababa, Makākkelaňňā</collection>
                  </msIdentifier>
                  <msContents>
                     <summary/>
                     <msItem xml:id="p1_i1">
                        <locus from="2a" to="164b">Fols 2a–164b</locus>
                        <title type="supplied">Commentary on the Gospel of Matthew.</title>
                        <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝʿǝz</textLang>
                        <note>Conclusion states that this commentary was composed in 1328 AG (1016/1017) and 400 AH (1009/1010) and was translated from Syriac to Arabic; Sources of the commentary are unnamed in this manuscript; Same commentary on the Gospels as British Library Orient. 731, British Library Orient. 732, and British Library Orient. 736. F. 1a blank.</note>
                        <incipit xml:lang="gez">መጽሐፈ፡ ልድቱ፡ ለኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ይቤ፡ መተርጕም፡ እስመ፡ ይትሐሠሡ፡ መተርጕማን፡ በእንተ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ክፍል፡ ኃተታ፡ ብዙኃ፡ ወምክንያቱሰ፡ ለቀዳማዊ፡ ዘበእንቲአሃ፡ ኢጸሐፈ፡ ማቴዎስ፡ በከመ፡ ልማደ፡ ነቢያት፡ ወካልአኒሁ፡ እለ፡ ቀደምዎ፡
                        </incipit>
                        <colophon xml:id="coloph1">Colophon was cut out and reinstated, but is illegible, fol. 165v</colophon>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
                  <physDesc>
